      • postDoctor

        @PostMapping(value="",
             consumes="application/x-www-form-urlencoded")
public java.lang.String postDoctor(@RequestBody
                                                                                                                     org.springframework.util.MultiValueMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> formData,
                                                                                                                     org.springframework.ui.Model model)
        This method will handle requests to create a new Doctor, along with its ShiftConfiguration
        Parameters:
        formData - The keys of the map will be the input names of edit-doctor form. E.g. "firstName". As input names can be repeated, the values of the map will be lists of Strings. Each String represents one of the values selected for a certain key. E.g. "wantedShit" = ["1", "2"]
        model - The model object that will be used to pass attributes to thymeleaf
        Returns:
        The path to the thymeleaf template used to represent the doctors list (The path is relative to resources/templates and does not contain the file extension)
